<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-537-103  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 537 103.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 2 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Greenpeace setting up on Suzy online system. (Stratford SoftwareCorp.'s Suzy on-line information service)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Stratford Software Corp. (information services).andO;Topic:     Information Storage and RetrievalInformation ServicesOn-LineGreenpeace.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>GREENPEACE SETTING UP ON SUZY ONLINE SYSTEM VANCOUVER, BRITISH COLUMBIA,CANADA, 1990 OCT 2 (NB) -- The Canadian arm of the international environmentorganization Greenpeace is setting up an information network on Suzy, theonline information service from Statford Software here.andM;Bob Lyons of Greenpeace Information in Vancouver told Newsbytes it is thefirst public-access online system Greenpeace has set up.andP;  The organizationhas used bulletin-board systems to keep in touch with grassrootsenvironmental groups in the United States, he said.andM;Lyons said Greenpeace chose Suzy because of its relatively low access costsand its ease of use.andP;  &quot;We're a non-profit organization,&quot; he explained, &quot;sowe're looking for something where not only business users but a privatecitizen can call up and get information.&quot;andM;The access software for Suzy sells for C$29.95 and access costs C$12 per hourin prime time and C$10 per off-peak hour.andM;Greenpeace will post its own press releases on Suzy, along withenvironment-related releases from government and business, Lyons said.andP;  Thenetwork will also let users exchange messages and participate in liveconferences on the environment.andM;(Grant Buckler/19901001/Press Contact: Terry McDonald, Stratford Software,604-439-1311; Bob Lyons, Greenpeace, 604-434-3042)</TEXT></DOC>